  "text": "The AQL query pipeline flows through these stages: (1) **Parsing** \u2014 `arangod/Aql/Parser.cpp` defines class `Parser` which parses AQL query text into an AST. (2) **Optimization** \u2014 `arangod/Aql/Optimizer.cpp` defines class `Optimizer` which transforms the AST into an optimized execution plan by applying optimizer rules. (3) **Execution** \u2014 `arangod/Aql/ExecutionEngine.cpp` defines class `ExecutionEngine` which orchestrates query plan execution, and `arangod/Aql/ExecutionBlock.cpp` defines class `ExecutionBlock` which is the base class for individual plan node executors. (4) **Storage retrieval** \u2014 `arangod/RocksDBEngine/RocksDBCollection.cpp` defines class `RocksDBCollection` (extends `RocksDBMetaCollection`) which provides the RocksDB storage engine interface for document reads/writes. (5) **Transaction management** \u2014 `arangod/Transaction/Methods.cpp` defines class `transaction::Methods` which provides the transactional API used by query execution, and `arangod/Transaction/Manager.cpp` defines class `transaction::Manager` which tracks and manages transaction state instances.",
